    "The primary objective of the CAE is to minimize the difference between the input data and the reconstructed data while taking the penalty term into account, promoting similarity in representations for similar input data.",
    "The overall loss function of CAE includes the reconstruction loss and a penalty term as follows:",
    "where ‖J F (X)‖ 2 F represents the squared Frobenius norm of the Jacobian matrix of the encoded representation concerning the input data.",
    "This norm measures the sensitivity of the encoded representation to small variations, calculated as:",
    "The standard Autoencoder may not emphasize the relationships between nearby data points during its learning process, which can lead to extracted features lacking crucial information about the data's internal structure."
